I think the poptrad concept of pornography sort of corrupting men's minds is a good way for women to process the perennial violence of human sexuality in the same way "AI" allows regular people to understand what Konrad Zuse style IBM punch card computers are actually capable of.

E.g. in a 14th century romance, Sir Gawain (who is supposed to be the most noble knight in the land) finds Gran de Lis alone and unprotected and his first thought is to violate her. Situating such dynamic under the sign of a more concrete and contemporary cause soothes our minds.

Similarly you could calculate the economy well in advance or organize a genocide using early computers that looked like a mix of furniture and an unusual sewing machine. But having a sort of character/tutelary spirit personifying the technology makes it more acute, real to others
